  <refnamediv>
    <refname>imlogpolar</refname>
    <refpurpose>Remaps an image to log-polar space.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   y = imlogpolar(x,m);
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x :</term>
      <listitem><para> Input image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>m :</term>
      <listitem><para> Magnitude scale parameter</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>y :</term>
      <listitem><para> Output image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The function cvLogPolar transforms the source image using the following transformation:
p = m*log(sqrt(x^2 + y^2)), phi = atan(y/x)
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/balloons.png"));
y = imlogpolar(x);
imshow(y);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

